{"id":951,"date":"2019-09-09T19:32:10","date_gmt":"2019-09-09T16:32:10","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/dev.atomicwallet.io\/?p=951"},"modified":"2021-06-17T16:43:18","modified_gmt":"2021-06-17T13:43:18","slug":"financial-advantages-of-atomic-swaps","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/academy\/financial-advantages-of-atomic-swaps","title":{"rendered":"Financial aspects of Atomic Swaps &#8211; Economy and Fees"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img  loading=\"lazy\"  width=\"800\"  height=\"270\"  src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABAQMAAAAl21bKAAAAA1BMVEUAAP+KeNJXAAAAAXRSTlMAQObYZgAAAAlwSFlzAAAOxAAADsQBlSsOGwAAAApJREFUCNdjYAAAAAIAAeIhvDMAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\"  alt=\"financial-advantages-of-atomic-swaps\"  class=\"wp-image-13817 pk-lazyload\"  data-pk-sizes=\"auto\"  data-ls-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"  data-pk-src=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/financial-advantages-of-atomic-swaps.png\"  data-pk-srcset=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/financial-advantages-of-atomic-swaps.png 800w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/financial-advantages-of-atomic-swaps-300x101.png 300w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/financial-advantages-of-atomic-swaps-768x259.png 768w\" ><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Fees are the cornerstone in the world of cryptocurrency and crypto-trading. All investors have to deal with several types of fees. This is a standard model: you pay for third-party services, just like in the classic stock market.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides, due to decentralized nature of cryptocurrency, you must pay for the use of blockchain. In addition to these fees, many wallets and stock exchanges charge their own fee for adding or withdrawing funds from the marketplace.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a result, there are three types of transaction fees for working with digital assets:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Fee for order execution<\/li><li>Transaction fee<\/li><li>Fee for adding and withdrawing funds<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The world of cryptocurrency is full of exchange services and exchanges, each of which has its own fee system. In this article, we will look at several popular resources for BTC\/LTC exchange and different exchange amounts in order to understand the difference between atomic swaps and traditional fee system.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img  loading=\"lazy\"  width=\"800\"  height=\"450\"  src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABAQMAAAAl21bKAAAAA1BMVEUAAP+KeNJXAAAAAXRSTlMAQObYZgAAAAlwSFlzAAAOxAAADsQBlSsOGwAAAApJREFUCNdjYAAAAAIAAeIhvDMAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\"  alt=\"Atomic Swaps Economy\"  class=\"wp-image-13829 pk-lazyload\"  data-pk-sizes=\"auto\"  data-ls-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"  data-pk-src=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-swaps-economy.png\"  data-pk-srcset=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-swaps-economy.png 300w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-swaps-economy.png 910w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-swaps-economy.png 768w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-swaps-economy.png 1920w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-swaps-economy.png 1536w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-swaps-economy.png 2048w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-swaps-economy.png 380w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-swaps-economy.png 800w\" ><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"atomic-swap-fee-in-atomic-wallet\">Atomic swap fee in Atomic Wallet<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Atomic swap operates in a fully decentralized way, which allows you to get rid of two types of fees at once. First, you do not have to pay intermediary fees (to exchange or exchanger) for crypto transaction. Secondly, the wallet itself does not require any payment for transactions. You only have to pay a fixed network fee, which does not depend on the amount of the currency exchanged.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img  loading=\"lazy\"  width=\"786\"  height=\"236\"  src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABAQMAAAAl21bKAAAAA1BMVEUAAP+KeNJXAAAAAXRSTlMAQObYZgAAAAlwSFlzAAAOxAAADsQBlSsOGwAAAApJREFUCNdjYAAAAAIAAeIhvDMAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\"  alt=\"Atomic Swaps Fee\"  class=\"wp-image-13841 pk-lazyload\"  data-pk-sizes=\"auto\"  data-ls-sizes=\"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px\"  data-pk-src=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/swaps-fee.png\"  data-pk-srcset=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/swaps-fee.png 300w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/swaps-fee.png 1024w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/swaps-fee.png 768w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/swaps-fee.png 1920w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/swaps-fee.png 1536w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/swaps-fee.png 2048w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/swaps-fee.png 380w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/swaps-fee.png 786w\" ><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A total fee: 1.4 USD<br>B total fee: 1.4 USD<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Transaction fee is constant for any swap amount in one moment.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img  loading=\"lazy\"  width=\"774\"  height=\"575\"  src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABAQMAAAAl21bKAAAAA1BMVEUAAP+KeNJXAAAAAXRSTlMAQObYZgAAAAlwSFlzAAAOxAAADsQBlSsOGwAAAApJREFUCNdjYAAAAAIAAeIhvDMAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\"  alt=\"Atomic Wallet Atomic Swaps\"  class=\"wp-image-13853 pk-lazyload\"  data-pk-sizes=\"auto\"  data-ls-sizes=\"(max-width: 774px) 100vw, 774px\"  data-pk-src=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-wallet-atomic-swap.png\"  data-pk-srcset=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-wallet-atomic-swap.png 272w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-wallet-atomic-swap.png 689w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-wallet-atomic-swap.png 768w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-wallet-atomic-swap.png 1454w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-wallet-atomic-swap.png 1536w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-wallet-atomic-swap.png 2048w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-wallet-atomic-swap.png 380w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/atomic-wallet-atomic-swap.png 774w\" ><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"okex-fee\">Okex fee<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Okex is one of the oldest and largest crypto exchanges. The estimated monthly audience is hundreds of thousands of users, and daily turnover exceeds 1.5 billion dollars.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Fees<\/li><li>Maker fee: 0.15%<\/li><li>Taker fee: 0.20%<\/li><li>1LTC = 93.9 USD*<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img  loading=\"lazy\"  width=\"736\"  height=\"256\"  src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABAQMAAAAl21bKAAAAA1BMVEUAAP+KeNJXAAAAAXRSTlMAQObYZgAAAAlwSFlzAAAOxAAADsQBlSsOGwAAAApJREFUCNdjYAAAAAIAAeIhvDMAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\"  alt=\"Okex Fee\"  class=\"wp-image-13865 pk-lazyload\"  data-pk-sizes=\"auto\"  data-ls-sizes=\"(max-width: 736px) 100vw, 736px\"  data-pk-src=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/okex-fee.png\"  data-pk-srcset=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/okex-fee.png 300w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/okex-fee.png 1024w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/okex-fee.png 736w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/okex-fee.png 1920w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/okex-fee.png 1536w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/okex-fee.png 2048w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/okex-fee.png 380w\" ><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"poloniex-fee\">Poloniex fee<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Poloniex platform, one of the largest US-based exchanges, presents another example of crypto-exchange fees.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/poloniex.com\/fees\/\">Fees<\/a><\/li><li>Maker fee: 0.10%<\/li><li>Taker fee: 0.20%<\/li><li>1LTC = 93.9 USD*<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img  loading=\"lazy\"  width=\"733\"  height=\"251\"  src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABAQMAAAAl21bKAAAAA1BMVEUAAP+KeNJXAAAAAXRSTlMAQObYZgAAAAlwSFlzAAAOxAAADsQBlSsOGwAAAApJREFUCNdjYAAAAAIAAeIhvDMAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\"  alt=\"Poloniex Fee\"  class=\"wp-image-13877 pk-lazyload\"  data-pk-sizes=\"auto\"  data-ls-sizes=\"(max-width: 733px) 100vw, 733px\"  data-pk-src=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/poloniex-fee.png\"  data-pk-srcset=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/poloniex-fee.png 733w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/poloniex-fee-300x103.png 300w\" ><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"changelly-fee\">Changelly Fee<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The next participant of our review is Changelly, a service for instant exchange of cryptocurrency, integrated into some of the largest exchanges, having a monthly turnover of more than $ 500 million.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/changelly.com\/faq#how-does-changelly-work\">Fees<\/a><\/li><li>1LTC = 93.9 USD*<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img  loading=\"lazy\"  width=\"788\"  height=\"266\"  src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABAQMAAAAl21bKAAAAA1BMVEUAAP+KeNJXAAAAAXRSTlMAQObYZgAAAAlwSFlzAAAOxAAADsQBlSsOGwAAAApJREFUCNdjYAAAAAIAAeIhvDMAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\"  alt=\"Changelly Fee\"  class=\"wp-image-13889 pk-lazyload\"  data-pk-sizes=\"auto\"  data-ls-sizes=\"(max-width: 788px) 100vw, 788px\"  data-pk-src=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/changelly-fee.png\"  data-pk-srcset=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/changelly-fee.png 300w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/changelly-fee.png 1024w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/changelly-fee.png 768w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/changelly-fee.png 1920w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/changelly-fee.png 1536w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/changelly-fee.png 2048w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/changelly-fee.png 380w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/changelly-fee.png 788w\" ><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see from the summary table, cryptocurrency exchange using atomic swap technology is beneficial for any transaction amount.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Calculations for exchange fees and Changelly service were made without taking into account the deposit fees. Fixed network fee for atomic swaps allows you to save a lot, while on exchanges the fee becomes higher in proportion to the increase in the amount of exchange.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img  loading=\"lazy\"  width=\"800\"  height=\"494\"  src=\"data:image\/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABAQMAAAAl21bKAAAAA1BMVEUAAP+KeNJXAAAAAXRSTlMAQObYZgAAAAlwSFlzAAAOxAAADsQBlSsOGwAAAApJREFUCNdjYAAAAAIAAeIhvDMAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\"  alt=\"Changelly Fee\"  class=\"wp-image-13901 pk-lazyload\"  data-pk-sizes=\"auto\"  data-ls-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"  data-pk-src=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/fees-comparison.png\"  data-pk-srcset=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/fees-comparison.png 300w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/fees-comparison.png 829w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/fees-comparison.png 768w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/fees-comparison.png 1749w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/fees-comparison.png 1536w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/fees-comparison.png 2048w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/fees-comparison.png 380w, https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/fees-comparison.png 800w\" ><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The technology integrated into Atomic Wallet solves multiple problems for a wide range of crypto-enthusiasts\u200a\u2014\u200afrom novice investors to large whales. Try Atomic Swap \u2014&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/atomicwallet.io\/\">https:\/\/atomicwallet.io<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>*Exchange rates provided by coinmarketcap.com on 14.06.18<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"Fees are the cornerstone in the world of cryptocurrency and crypto-trading. All investors have to deal with several types of fees. This is a standard model: you pay for third-party services, just like in the classic stock market.\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":952,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[14],"tags":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v14.4.1 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Financial aspects of Atomic Swaps - Economy and Fees<\/title>\n<meta na